# Consistent line endings across platforms.
#
# Store text files as LF in the repository AND keep LF in the working tree
# (this repo's files are already LF). With core.autocrlf=true on Windows, a
# text file without an explicit rule is otherwise expected to be CRLF on
# checkout, which shows up as a phantom "modified" with a zero content diff
# (e.g. src-tauri/Cargo.toml). Pinning text to LF removes that ambiguity.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicitly binary — never apply line-ending normalization to these.
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.webp binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf  binary
*.otf  binary
*.wasm binary
*.icns binary
